  "prompt": "How do you say goodbye to a dying loved one?",
  "response": "Saying goodbye to a dying loved one is an incredibly personal and difficult experience. Here are some suggestions that might help you navigate this painful time:\n\n1. **Express Your Love**: Tell them how much you love them. Share specific memories that highlight your feelings and the bond you share.\n\n2. **Be Present**: If possible, spend time with them. Hold their hand, sit with them, and offer comfort through your physical presence.\n\n3. **Listen**: Allow them to express their feelings and thoughts if they are able to. Sometimes, just being a listener is the most comforting thing you can do.\n\n4. **Say What You Need to Say**: If there are unresolved issues or things you've always wanted to say, now might be the time to voice them, gently and lovingly.\n\n5. **Reassure Them**: If appropriate, reassure them that it\u2019s okay to let go and that you will be alright. This can provide a sense of peace.\n\n6. **Create a Peaceful Environment**: Surround them with comfort, whether it's through soft music, favorite items, or a serene atmosphere.\n\n7. **Celebrate Their Life**: Share stories and memories that celebrate their life and the impact they've had on you and others.\n\n8. **Seek Support**: Don\u2019t hesitate to reach out to friends, family, or professionals for support during this challenging time.\n\nRemember, there is no right or wrong way to say goodbye. Trust your instincts and do what feels right for both you and your loved one.",
